OL,3,CFrom ministers to NHS doctors: Who is
OL,4,Cto blame for the infected blood
OL,5,Cscandal?
OL,7,FThe lives of more than 30,000 people
OL,8,Fin the UK were upended after they were
OL,9,Finfected with diseases linked to
OL,10,Fcontaminated blood products during the
OL,11,F1970s and 1980s.
OL,13,FThe diseases - Hepatitis C and HIV -
OL,14,Fresulted in the deaths of around 3,000
OL,15,Fpatients - 380 of which were children.
