OL,3,CFrom ministers to NHS doctors: Who is
OL,4,Cto blame for the infected blood
OL,5,Cscandal?
OL,7,FThe risks of blood and blood products
OL,8,Fcausing severe infection were "known
OL,9,Fwell before most patients were
OL,10,Ftreated," the report found.
OL,12,FYet, patients were not informed of the
OL,13,Frisks or the alternatives, with a
OL,14,Fculture of "doctor knows best"
OL,15,Fprevailing among the ranks of the NHS.
OL,17,FIn some cases, patients were not even
OL,18,Ftold they had been infected, whilst
OL,19,Fothers were informed, but in ways that
OL,20,Fwere "insensitive and inappropriate,"
OL,21,Fthe report found.
